iMAP.name: iMAP
iMAP.description: This MIB defines the managed objects that are used by the function interfaces of the SNMP Northbound Interface.

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationV2.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationV2
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationV2.description: Root node for the converted TRAP-TYPEs. It contains the Heartbeat Notification Trap

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationType.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationType
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatNotificationType.description: The iMAP sends the heartbeat notification trap to the NMS regularly each period. If the NMS receives the trap, the connection between the NMS and the iMAP works. If not, the connection fails.

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSystemLabel.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSystemLabel
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSystemLabel.description: Managed system ID: indicates the managed system from which the heartbeat notification is reported. It uniquely identifies one EMS.

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatPeriod.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatPeriod
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatPeriod.description: Heartbeat period (must be between 3 and 300), in seconds

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatTimeStamp.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatTimeStamp
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatTimeStamp.description: Time stamp: the time when the heartbeat notification is generated

iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSvcReportInterval.name: iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSvcReportInterval
iMAPNorthboundHeartbeatSvcReportInterval.description: Accepts integral values in the range 3-300 (both end inclusive) Sets heartbeat interval to the value supplied. A heart beat is sent immediately consisting of changed interval. Attempt to set with invalid value results in error.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmQuery.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmQuery
iMAPNorthboundAlarmQuery.description: Accepts only values 0 and 1 (single character) Attempt to set any other value returns error 1-> starts query active alarm process (if previous query alarm process is in progress then error is returned) 0-> stops the previous query active alarm process in progress (if any)

iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmNotificationV2.name: iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmNotificationV2
iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmNotificationV2.description: Root node for the converted TRAP-TYPEs. It contains the Fault Alarm Traps for sending real-time alarms to NMS

iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmReportNotificati.name: iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmReportNotificationType
iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmReportNotificati.description: The iMAP system sends real-time alarms to the NMS using this trap. If an alarm occurs to an NE or the iMAP, the iMAP sends the alarm trap to the NMS.

iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryBeginNotifi.name: iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryBeginNotificationType
iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryBeginNotifi.description: The iMAP notifies the NMS of the start of the query. After the NMS receives the active alarm query start trap, the query starts. The trap is triggered by NMS for alarm query.

iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryNotificatio.name: iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryNotificationType
iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryNotificatio.description: The iMAP system sends queried alarms to the NMS using this trap.

iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryEndNotifica.name: iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryEndNotificationType
iMAPNorthboundFaultAlarmQueryEndNotifica.description: The iMAP notifies the NMS of the stop of the query. After the NMS receives the active alarm query stop trap, it indicates that the query ends. The NMS triggers the stop of the query, or the query ends after the NMS receives the active alarms.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmCSN.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmCSN
iMAPNorthboundAlarmCSN.description: Serial number of the alarm > 0. An alarm is identified by a unique number.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmCategory.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmCategory
iMAPNorthboundAlarmCategory.description: Category can be one of the following: 1 - Fault 2 - Clear 3 - Event 4 - Acknowledge 5 - Unacknowledge 9 - Change

iMAPNorthboundAlarmOccurTime.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmOccurTime
iMAPNorthboundAlarmOccurTime.description: Fault occurrence time, time at which the alarm has been raised

iMAPNorthboundAlarmMOName.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmMOName
iMAPNorthboundAlarmMOName.description: Managed object name for which the alarm has been generated

iMAPNorthboundAlarmProductID.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmProductID
iMAPNorthboundAlarmProductID.description: Product type ID: 1 - transmission 2 - mobile 3 - fixed network narrowband 4 - fixed network broadband 5 - intelligent network 6 - omc

iMAPNorthboundAlarmNEDevID.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmNEDevID
iMAPNorthboundAlarmNEDevID.description: Network Element ID or Device ID

iMAPNorthboundAlarmDevCsn.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmDevCsn
iMAPNorthboundAlarmDevCsn.description: Serial number of the alarm device, unique in the same NE.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmID.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmID
iMAPNorthboundAlarmID.description: Alarm ID of the generated alarm

iMAPNorthboundAlarmType.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmType
iMAPNorthboundAlarmType.description: Alarm type. It can be one of the following: 1 - Power System 2 - Environment System 3 - Signaling System 4 - Trunk System 5 - Hardware System 6 - Software System 7 - Running System 8 - Communication System 9 - QoS 10 - Processing error 11 - OMC

iMAPNorthboundAlarmLevel.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmLevel
iMAPNorthboundAlarmLevel.description: Level is the alarm severity. It can be one of the following: 1 - Critical 2 - Major 3 - Minor 4 - Warning 6 - Cleared

iMAPNorthboundAlarmOperator.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmOperator
iMAPNorthboundAlarmOperator.description: Operator, who performs the acknowledgement and clearance operations.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmParas10.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmParas10
iMAPNorthboundAlarmParas10.description: Original alarm level, defined by the device when the alarm is generated. 1 Critical 2 Major 3 Minor 4 Warning

iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendInfo.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendInfo
iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendInfo.description: Extended information (max: 250 characters) Alarm extended information, including the location information of the alarm.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmProbablecause.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmProbablecause
iMAPNorthboundAlarmProbablecause.description: Probable cause of the alarm (max: 250 characters)

iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendProductItem1.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendProductItem1
iMAPNorthboundAlarmExtendProductItem1.description: This is one of 15 extensible alarm fields to be reported as part of alarm information. The fields to be reported are decided by the configuration for the SNMP agent in file snmpsvc.xml. For string type parameters the maximum supported length is 250 characters. If string is longer it will be truncated to 250 characters.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearOperator.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearOperator
iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearOperator.description: The operator who cleared this alarm.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmObjectInstanceType.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmObjectInstanceType
iMAPNorthboundAlarmObjectInstanceType.description: Object instance type for the raised alarm

iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearCategory.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearCategory
iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearCategory.description: This specifies the Clear Category of alarms. 0 1 - ADAC (Automatically Detected Automcatically Cleared) 2 - ADMC (Automatically Detected Manually Cleared)

iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearType.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearType
iMAPNorthboundAlarmClearType.description: This specifies the Clear Type of alarms. 0 1 - Normal Clear 2 - Restore Clear 3 - Manual Clear 4 - Configure Clear 5 - Co-relation Clear

iMAPNorthboundAlarmServiceAffectFlag.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmServiceAffectFlag
iMAPNorthboundAlarmServiceAffectFlag.description: Affecting service flag for the alarm

iMAPNorthboundAlarmAcknowledge.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmAcknowledge
iMAPNorthboundAlarmAcknowledge.description: Give serial number(s) of alarms to be acknowledged. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s) are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be acknowledged. This also contains invalid Alarm serial number(s). If all alarms are successfully acknowledged then output is blank.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmUnAcknowledge.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmUnAcknowledge
iMAPNorthboundAlarmUnAcknowledge.description: Give serial number(s) of alarms to be unacknowledged. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s) are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be unacknowledged. This also contains invalid Alarm serial number(s). If all alarms are successfully unacknowledged then output is blank.

iMAPNorthboundAlarmClear.name: iMAPNorthboundAlarmClear
iMAPNorthboundAlarmClear.description: Give serial number(s) of alarms to be cleared. Multiple serial numbers are separated by comma(,). Alarms serial number(s)are of type unsigned long and incompatible types are automatically considered as invalid serial number(s). Get attempt on this node will result in error. Output: Serial number(s) of alarms which could not be cleared. This also contains invalid Alarm serial number(s). If all alarms are successfully cleared then output is blank.
